<span class="PRTitle"><!-- NewsTitle.start -->Zubiri reveals rampant cheating in Metro Manila during the 2007 elections<!-- NewsTitle.end --></span>
</p>
<!-- NewsBody.start -->


<p style="text-align: justify">Senator Juan Miguel "Migz" Zubiri today presented to the media documents showing massive cheating and syndicated election operations in precincts level in Metro Manila during the 2007 elections.</p>

<p style="text-align: justify">"So far ang na revised na naming precincts sa aking counter protest ay 44, 333 as of July 8 2011 on my 75% counter protest. The number of votes deducted from Pimentel as of July 8, 2011 have been 53,490. This has been confirmed by the SET through our revisors and their revisors, so iyan po ang sinasabi nating mga sindikatong gumalaw nuong 2007 elections kung saan precinct level po ang kanilang dayaan. These are the actual findings hindi po iyan gawa-gawa lang namin or figment of our imagination," Zubiri said adding that: "the total ballots objected is 157, 913. Broken down as follows: ballots written by one or two persons ay 142,449 - iyan po ay kino-contest namin dito sa aking 75%, halata pong maraming lugar sa nabuksan namin dito sa Metro Manila na halatang isang kamay lang po ang ginamit para isulat itong mga balotang ito. Dito naman sa fake or marked spurious ballots ang lumalabas po ay 15, 464 ang aming nahanap pa at hindi pa tapos ang bilangan dito sa Metro Manila."</p>

